specs/t-003b-spec.md:1:# Task T-003b: Coupling Multiplier From Bus Value
specs/t-003b-spec.md:5:T-003a added a Python-side reader for the shared `affective_state_bus`, but the
specs/t-003b-spec.md:6:voice layer still lacks a pure helper that turns a bus value into the coupling
specs/t-003b-spec.md:8:multiplier into per-voice modulator depths; this task provides the small,
specs/t-003b-spec.md:26:  `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/senseweave_voice.py` next to the
specs/t-003b-spec.md:27:  existing `read_affective_state_bus(...)` helper.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:28:- Name the helper `coupling_multiplier_from_bus_value(...)` to make the input
specs/t-003b-spec.md:30:- Accept `bus_value: float` and keyword-only `coupling_strength: float = 0.5`,
specs/t-003b-spec.md:31:  matching the PRD's default per-voice coupling strength.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:32:- Clamp `bus_value` to the shared affective-state bus range `[0.0, 1.0]`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:35:- Return `1.0 + clamped_coupling_strength * clamped_bus_value`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:42:- `bus_value=0.0` returns `1.0` with default strength.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:43:- `bus_value=0.5` returns `1.25` with default strength `0.5`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:44:- `bus_value=1.0` returns `1.5` with default strength `0.5`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:45:- Negative bus values clamp to `0.0`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:46:- Bus values above `1.0` clamp to `1.0`.
specs/t-003b-spec.md:55:1. The pure multiplier helper returns the PRD boundary values for bus values
specs/t-003b-spec.md:57:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_senseweave_voice.py::TestCouplingMultiplier::test_default_strength_boundary_values -q`
specs/t-003b-spec.md:59:2. The pure multiplier helper clamps bus values and coupling strengths into
specs/t-003b-spec.md:61:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_senseweave_voice.py::TestCouplingMultiplier::test_clamps_bus_value_and_coupling_strength -q`
