    test(synthesis): pin voice fx_bus_id routing against cross-voice leakage [T-044c]
    
    Extend `TestFxBusRouting` with two regression tests that pin the
    per-voice FX bus contract beyond the positive match already covered
    in T-044b:
    
    * `test_note_on_rejects_other_voices_fx_bus_ids` — for each profiled
      timbre, the emitted `fx_bus_id` must equal the voice's own profile
      bus and must not match any other voice's profile bus, so a
      profile-lookup drift cannot silently route one voice through
      another voice's reverb return.
    
    * `test_set_timbre_reroutes_to_the_new_voices_fx_bus_id` — swapping
      timbre via `set_timbre` and re-emitting must carry the new voice's
      profile bus, with no stale bus id from the prior timbre present in
      the `/s_new` args.
    
    Mutation-tested: bumping the emitted bus by +1 in
    `SenseweaveVoice.note_on` causes both new tests to fail.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
test(synthesis): pin voice fx_bus_id routing against cross-voice leakage [T-044c]

Extend `TestFxBusRouting` with two regression tests that pin the
per-voice FX bus contract beyond the positive match already covered
in T-044b:

* `test_note_on_rejects_other_voices_fx_bus_ids` — for each profiled
  timbre, the emitted `fx_bus_id` must equal the voice's own profile
  bus and must not match any other voice's profile bus, so a
  profile-lookup drift cannot silently route one voice through
  another voice's reverb return.

* `test_set_timbre_reroutes_to_the_new_voices_fx_bus_id` — swapping
  timbre via `set_timbre` and re-emitting must carry the new voice's
  profile bus, with no stale bus id from the prior timbre present in
  the `/s_new` args.

Mutation-tested: bumping the emitted bus by +1 in
`SenseweaveVoice.note_on` causes both new tests to fail.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>


